events.description:
If Donald Trump has taken any presidential actions on February 12 (as checked on the “Presidential Actions” page at whitehouse.gov at 10:00 AM ET on February 13), then the market resolves to "Yes". Otherwise, this market will resolve "No". 

The market solely resolves to the publication date visibly displayed on the home page of the "Presidential Actions" tab at whitehouse.gov the following day at 10:00 AM. The actions may include proclamations, executive orders, nominations & appointments, and memoranda. Any item listed on the page counts, regardless of its legal effect.

Examples (from Jan 10, 2026):
Executive Order with a Jan 7 signing date is released with a Jan 10 publication date → resolves Yes
Proclamation e-mailed to White House Press Pool but not uploaded by 10:00 AM next day → resolves No
Proclamation is released Jan 10 with a backdated Jan 9 publication date → resolves No
Bill signed into law and shows up on "Briefings & Statements" instead of "Presidential Actions" → resolves No

The resolution source is the "Presidential Actions" page on whitehouse.gov (see: https://www.whitehouse.gov/presidential-actions/)
events.title: Will Trump do anything on February 12?
